H0.text: What city is famously 5,280 feet above sea level. Albuquerque

H1.text: What city is famously 5,280 feet above sea level. Salt Lake City

H2.text: What city is famously 5,280 feet above sea level. Cheyenne

H3.text: What city is famously 5,280 feet above sea level. Denver

A4.text: Denver's nickname is the 'Mile-High City', as its official elevation is one mile (5,280 ft; 1,609 m) above sea level, defined by the elevation of the spot of a benchmark on the steps of the State Capitol building.

A5.text: The elevation of the entire city ranges from 5,130 to 5,690 feet (1,560 to 1,730 m).
